
[1]constitutional

   CONSTITUTIONAL, a.

   1. Bred or inherent in the constitution, or in the natural frame of
   body or mind; as a constitutional infirmity; constitutional ardor or
   dulness.

   2. Consistent with the constitution; authorized by the constitution or
   fundamental rules of a government; legal.

   An act of Congress prohibiting the importation of slaves into the
   United States is constitutional.

   3. Relating to the constitution; as a constitutional doubt.
